{"lemma":"كُراتُ","slug":"كُراتُ","root":"ك.ر.#","root_slug":"ك-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كُرَة","root":"كره","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36803"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ball","examples":[{"text":"الكرة مستديرة وملونة.","english":"The ball is round and colorful."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sphere, globe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"recurrence, repetition, return, time","examples":[{"text":"لَوْ أَنَّ لِي كَرَّةً فَأَكُونَ مِنَ الْمُحْسِنِينَ","english":"If I had another time so I could be amongst those who do good!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attack, instance noun of كَرّ (karr)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Likely through Aramaic, from Akkadian 𒄥 (/⁠kurru⁠/), ultimately from Sumerian 𒄥 (GUR, “a bundle, rolled up barley”)"},"ipa":["/ku.ra/","/kar.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36803","headword_ar":"كَرَّةٌ","root":"kr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A return."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) So in the Kur, [ii. 162,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo A^an~a lanaA kar~apF","text_ar":"لَوْ اَنَّ لَنَا كَرَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that there were for us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a return"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the world, or former state. And so in xxvi. 102, and xxxix. 59. (Jel.) And so in the saying of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~`ha All~`ha","text_ar":"اللّٰهَ اللّٰهَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lokar~apa EalaY nabiy~ikumo","text_ar":"وَا@لْكَرَّةَ عَلَى نَبِيِّكُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear ye God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear ye God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and return to your prophet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return to life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resurrection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"renewal of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the creation, after perishing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A return to the fight, after wheeling away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retiring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and simply,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a charge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in war;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kur~aY","text_ar":"كُرَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kar~aAtN","text_ar":"كَرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time; one time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sense of the French"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fois"},{"kind":"text","text":"”; generally repeated, or used in the pl. form, so as to denote a returning to an action, once, or more; i. e., repetition, or reiteration, thereof, agreeably with the primary signification;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~apN","text_ar":"مَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) pl. as above. (S.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalahu kar~apF baEoda kar~apK","text_ar":"فَعَلَهُ كَرَّةً بَعْدَ كَرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did it time after time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalahu kar~aAtK","text_ar":"فَعَلَهُ كَرَّاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did it several times"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b5-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A turn to prevail against an opposing party; victory."},{"kind":"text","text":"So in the Kur, [xvii. 6,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a radadonaA lakumu","text_ar":"ثُمَّ رَدَدْنَا لَكُمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkar~apa Ealayohimo","text_ar":"الكَرَّةَ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then we gave to you the turn to prevail against them; the victory over them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd, Jel.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","Sgh","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}